  "text": "Prometheus web UI authentication controls are implemented through the following mechanisms:\n\n## Admin API Access Control\nThe primary authentication mechanism within Prometheus itself is admin API access control. The API struct in `web/api/v1/api.go` (line 224) contains an `enableAdmin` boolean field (line 241) that controls access to sensitive database operations.\n\nThe `NewAPI` function (line 267) accepts an `enableAdmin` parameter (line 281) that is assigned to the API struct (line 324). This parameter is set based on the `--web.enable-admin-api` command-line flag defined in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` (lines 401-403).\n\nThe `API.Register` method (line 392 in `api.go`) registers three admin endpoints:\n- `/admin/tsdb/delete_series` (POST/PUT)\n- `/admin/tsdb/clean_tombstones` (POST/PUT)\n- `/admin/tsdb/snapshot` (POST/PUT)\n\nThese endpoints are implemented by the following methods, each checking the `enableAdmin` flag:\n- `API.deleteSeries` (line 2026) - checks `!api.enableAdmin` at line 2027\n- `API.snapshot` (line 2059) - checks `!api.enableAdmin` at line 2060\n- `API.cleanTombstones` (line 2093) - checks `!api.enableAdmin` at line 2094\n\nWhen `enableAdmin` is false, these methods return an `apiError` with status code 503 (Unavailable) and the message \"admin APIs disabled\".\n\n## Web Server Setup\nThe `Handler` struct in `web/web.go` manages the HTTP server setup. The `Handler.Run` method (line 722) initializes the HTTP server and calls `toolkit_web.ServeMultiple` (line 760) from the external `github.com/prometheus/exporter-toolkit/web` library, passing the web configuration file path.\n\n## BasicAuth Middleware and TLS Client Certificate Validation\nThe BasicAuth middleware and TLS client certificate validation are implemented in the external `github.com/prometheus/exporter-toolkit/web` library (not part of prometheus/prometheus). These are enabled through the web configuration file specified by the `--web.config.file` flag (defined in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` lines 401-403) and validated via `toolkit_web.Validate()` (line 1145 in `main.go`).\n\nThe web configuration file allows enabling TLS and basic authentication for the entire web UI, complementing the admin API access control for more granular per-endpoint authorization."
